{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015pxq9iZvVCwbV9PQn8WR4f","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstepsCompleted: ['step-01-init', 'step-02-discovery', 'step-02b-vision', 'step-02c-executive-summary', 'step-03-success', 'step-04-journeys', 'step-05-domain', 'step-06-innovation', 'step-07-project-type', 'step-08-scoping', 'step-09-functional', 'step-10-nonfunctional', 'step-11-polish', 'step-12-complete']\n3\tclassification:\n4\t  projectType: developer_tool\n5\t  domain: general\n6\t  complexity: high\n7\t  projectContext: brownfield\n8\tinputDocuments:\n9\t  - prd-multi-framework.md (multi-framework orchestration PRD, brownfield context)\n10\t  - architecture-multi-framework.md (architecture with workflow engine details)\n11\t  - quick-spec-session-telemetry-retro-split.md (telemetry/retro quick spec)\n12\tdocumentCounts:\n13\t  briefs: 0\n14\t  research: 0\n15\t  brainstorming: 0\n16\t  projectDocs: 3\n17\tworkflowType: 'prd'\n18\t---\n19\t\n20\t# Product Requirements Document - codeharness\n21\t\n22\t**Author:** BMad\n23\t**Date:** 2026-04-03\n24\t\n25\t## Executive Summary\n26\t\n27\tcodeharness currently executes stories sequentially — one at a time, one framework at a time. A 19-story sprint takes 8+ hours of wall-clock time. This PRD adds **parallel execution** at two levels: parallel epics via git worktrees and parallel stories within epics, cutting sprint time proportionally to the parallelism factor.\n28\t\n29\tThe workflow engine gains a **hierarchical flow model** with three levels. Sprint-level flow schedules epics (potentially in parallel). Epic-level flow schedules stories and runs an epic retro on completion. Story-level flow is the existing `implement → verify → loop` pipeline. Each level has distinct lifecycle hooks: per-story telemetry (zero-token, engine-handled) and per-epic retrospectives (LLM-powered, one call per epic instead of per-session).\n30\t\n31\tParallel execution requires **isolation**. Each parallel dispatch gets its own git worktree — a separate working directory on a separate branch. Stories within a worktree execute sequentially. When an epic completes, its worktree branch merges back to main. If merge conflicts occur, a merge agent resolves them with context from both branches.\n32\t\n33\tThree additional optimizations ship with this: **`agent: null` tasks** let the engine handle telemetry without LLM dispatch (saving ~$120-180/sprint on retro overhead), **verify flag propagation** moves flag-setting from the evaluator to the engine (fixing unreliable verification), and **coverage deduplication** eliminates redundant coverage runs during verification.\n34\t\n35\t### What Makes This Special\n36\t\n37\t- **Worktree-isolated parallelism** — each parallel epic runs in its own git worktree. No shared mutable state during execution. Conflicts surface only at merge time, handled by a merge agent.\n38\t- **Hierarchical flow model** — sprint → epic → story, each with its own lifecycle. Not a flat task queue — a structured execution DAG with dependency-aware scheduling.\n39\t- **Zero-token engine tasks** — `agent: null` tasks execute without LLM dispatch. Telemetry collection, flag setting, and state bookkeeping become free operations.\n40\t- **Multi-lane TUI** — parallel execution visualized as concurrent workflow lanes, each showing its own story progress, driver, and cost.\n41\t- **Proportional speedup** — 2 parallel worktrees = ~2x faster sprints. Configurable up from there.\n42\t\n43\t## Project Classification\n44\t\n45\t- **Project Type:** Developer tool — npm CLI extending existing workflow engine\n46\t- **Domain:** General software development tooling\n47\t- **Complexity:** High — git worktree lifecycle, multi-process orchestration, merge conflict resolution, hierarchical state machines, multi-lane TUI rendering\n48\t- **Project Context:** Brownfield — workflow engine, driver layer, TUI, state management all exist. This adds parallelism, hierarchy, and merge on top.\n49\t\n50\t## Success Criteria\n51\t\n52\t### User Success\n53\t\n54\t- **Sprint time reduction:** 2x parallel execution delivers ~2x wall-clock speedup. Target: 19-story sprint in <4h (vs current 8h+).\n55\t- **Zero merge failures:** Worktree isolation prevents file conflicts during execution. Merge agent resolves conflicts automatically. Target: <5% require manual intervention.\n56\t- **Retro cost elimination:** Per-session LLM retros replaced by zero-token telemetry. Target: $0 token cost for per-story data collection.\n57\t- **Parallel visibility:** User sees all active lanes in TUI — which epics running, which stories active, cost per lane.\n58\t\n59\t### Business Success\n60\t\n61\t- **3-month goal:** Parallel epic execution with worktrees, merge agent, and cross-worktree test validation working end-to-end. 2x speedup demonstrated.\n62\t- **6-month goal:** Parallel stories within epics. DAG-based scheduling. Configurable parallelism at 3-4 lanes.\n63\t- **Cost reduction:** ~$120-180/sprint from retro optimization. Additional savings from reduced wall-clock time.\n64\t\n65\t### Technical Success\n66\t\n67\t- **Worktree lifecycle:** Create, execute, merge, cleanup — fully automated. No orphaned worktrees.\n68\t- **State consistency:** Hierarchical state consistent across parallel worktrees. No corruption from concurrent writes.\n69\t- **Merge reliability:** Merge agent resolves conflicts on first attempt for >95% of merges.\n70\t- **Cross-worktree validation:** Full test suite passes on merged result before accepting.\n71\t- **TUI responsiveness:** Multi-lane rendering at 15 FPS with 2-4 concurrent lanes.\n72\t- **Backward compatibility:** `max_parallel: 1` produces identical behavior to current sequential execution.\n73\t\n74\t### Measurable Outcomes\n75\t\n76\t| Metric | Target | Method |\n77\t|--------|--------|--------|\n78\t| Sprint wall-clock time | <50% of sequential | Timed comparison |\n79\t| Merge conflict auto-resolution | >95% | Tracked per sprint |\n80\t| Retro token cost per story | $0 | Telemetry |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01GYH6ggx8N6jTTqCzjbiH3g","session_id":"3330d992-072a-4898-af8b-5f3f7e12cbac","uuid":"048a08af-773f-4182-b99b-86a368d70150","timestamp":"2026-04-03T17:38:32.241Z"}
