{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GYH6ggx8N6jTTqCzjbiH3g","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file created at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-3-telemetry-writer.md` (195 lines).\n\n**Story Details:**\n- Story ID: 16.3\n- Story Key: 16-3-telemetry-writer\n- File: `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-3-telemetry-writer.md`\n- Status: ready-for-dev\n- Sprint-status.yaml: NOT modified (per instructions)\n\n**What was created:**\n- 10 acceptance criteria, all tagged `<!-- verification: test-provable -->` — every AC is verifiable by building and running tests (no running app or environment needed since this is a pure data module with file I/O)\n- 3 task groups: create telemetry-writer.ts, replace no-op placeholder in registry, write unit tests (11 test cases)\n- Dev notes with architecture constraints, interface definitions, data extraction logic, performance requirements, and full reference chain to previous stories and planning artifacts\n\n**Key decisions:**\n- All 10 ACs are `test-provable` because the module is pure file I/O (appendFileSync/readFileSync) with no CLI, server, or environment dependencies\n- `epicId` extracted from `storyKey` by splitting on `-` and taking the first segment\n- `attempts` and `errors` fields set to `null`/`[]` because `TaskContext` doesn't carry them\n- Corrupted JSON line handling specified explicitly (AC #10) to prevent brittle retro reads\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **No config.yaml found** at `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` — the workflow references this but the file doesn't exist. Proceeded without it; the config variables (`user_name`, `communication_language`, etc.) were not critical for story creation.\n- **Sprint-status.yaml not updated** per explicit user instruction. The workflow normally marks the story as `ready-for-dev` in sprint-status.yaml. The sprint-status still shows `16-3-telemetry-writer: backlog`.\n- **No w