{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QaEq9z8kec1Ua6qqYLytuc","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 16.3: Telemetry Writer\n2\t\n3\tStatus: ready-for-dev\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want structured telemetry written as NDJSON after each story completes,\n9\tso that epic retros have rich data without per-session LLM cost.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** a new `src/lib/telemetry-writer.ts`, **when** imported, **then** it exports `writeTelemetryEntry(ctx: TaskContext): Promise<NullTaskResult>` and `readTelemetryForEpic(epicId: string): TelemetryEntry[]`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n14\t\n15\t2. **Given** the `telemetry` null task handler runs after a story completes, **when** it writes to `.codeharness/telemetry.jsonl`, **then** each line is valid JSON containing: `version` (number), `timestamp` (ISO 8601 string), `storyKey` (string), `epicId` (string), `duration_ms` (number), `cost_usd` (number|null), `attempts` (number|null), `acResults` (array|null), `filesChanged` (array), `testResults` (object|null), `errors` (array). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n16\t\n17\t3. **Given** the `TaskContext` passed to the handler, **when** a field is not available (e.g., no output contract, no test results), **then** the corresponding telemetry field is set to `null` — never fabricated or defaulted to a truthy value. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t4. **Given** the telemetry file `.codeharness/telemetry.jsonl`, **when** `writeTelemetryEntry` is called, **then** it appends one line using `appendFileSync` (not truncate/rewrite) and creates the `.codeharness/` directory if it does not exist. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t5. **Given** every telemetry entry, **when** serialized, **then** it includes `version: 1` as the first field for forward compatibility with future schema changes. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t6. **Given** `readTelemetryForEpic(\"16\")` is called, **when** the telemetry file contains entries for multiple epics, **then** it returns only entries whose `epicId` matches `\"16\"`, preserving insertion order. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t7. **Given** the `telemetry` handler is registered in `null-task-registry.ts`, **when** the engine reaches the `telemetry` task, **then** the real `writeTelemetryEntry` from `telemetry-writer.ts` is called instead of the current no-op placeholder. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t8. **Given** a telemetry write operation, **when** timed, **then** it completes in <10ms for a single NDJSON append (NFR3). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t9. **Given** the telemetry file does not exist, **when** `readTelemetryForEpic` is called, **then** it returns an empty array (not an error). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n30\t\n31\t10. **Given** a corrupted line in the telemetry file (invalid JSON), **when** `readTelemetryForEpic` reads it, **then** the corrupted line is skipped and remaining valid lines are returned. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n34\t\n35\t- [ ] Task 1: Create `src/lib/telemetry-writer.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #5)\n36\t  - [ ] Define `TelemetryEntry` interface with all required fields (`version`, `timestamp`, `storyKey`, `epicId`, `duration_ms`, `cost_usd`, `attempts`, `acResults`, `filesChanged`, `testResults`, `errors`)\n37\t  - [ ] Implement `writeTelemetryEntry(ctx: TaskContext): Promise<NullTaskResult>`:\n38\t    - Extract `epicId` from `ctx.storyKey` (split on first `-`, take first segment)\n39\t    - Build `TelemetryEntry` from `ctx` fields, setting `null` for unavailable data\n40\t    - Use `mkdirSync` to ensure `.codeharness/` exists (with `{ recursive: true }`)\n41\t    - Use `appendFileSync` to write JSON line + `\\n`\n42\t    - Return `{ success: true, output: 'telemetry: entry written for {storyKey}' }`\n43\t  - [ ] Implement `readTelemetryForEpic(epicId: string): TelemetryEntry[]`:\n44\t    - Read file with `readFileSync`, split on `\\n`, filter empty lines\n45\t    - Parse each line with `JSON.parse`, catch and skip corrupted lines\n46\t    - Filter by `epicId` match, return array\n47\t    - Return `[]` if file does not exist\n48\t\n49\t- [ ] Task 2: Replace no-op placeholder in `null-task-registry.ts` (AC: #7)\n50\t  - [ ] Import `writeTelemetryEntry` from `./telemetry-writer.js`\n51\t  - [ ] Replace the no-op `telemetry` handler with `writeTelemetryEntry`\n52\t\n53\t- [ ] Task 3: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#10)\n54\t  - [ ] Test: `writeTelemetryEntry` creates `.codeharness/` directory if missing\n55\t  - [ ] Test: `writeTelemetryEntry` appends one valid NDJSON line per call\n56\t  - [ ] Test: entry contains all required fields with correct types\n57\t  - [ ] Test: `version` field is `1` in every entry\n58\t  - [ ] Test: unavailable fields are `null` (no output contract scenario)\n59\t  - [ ] Test: `readTelemetryForEpic` filters entries by epicId\n60\t  - [ ] Test: `readTelemetryForEpic` returns `[]` when file does not exist\n61\t  - [ ] Test: `readTelemetryForEpic` skips corrupted JSON lines\n62\t  - [ ] Test: write completes in <10ms (performance assertion)\n63\t  - [ ] Test: multiple sequential writes produce multiple lines\n64\t  - [ ] Test: registered handler in null-task-registry calls `writeTelemetryEntry`\n65\t\n66\t## Dev Notes\n67\t\n68\t### Architecture Constraints\n69\t\n70\t- **New file:** `src/lib/telemetry-writer.ts` — pure data module. No side effects on import except function exports.\n71\t- **Modified file:** `src/lib/null-task-registry.ts` — replace the no-op `telemetry` placeholder (line 94-96) with the real handler from `telemetry-writer.ts`.\n72\t- **No new dependencies.** Use only `node:fs` and `node:path`. No external libraries.\n73\t- **ESM module** — use `.js` extensions in imports (e.g., `import { writeTelemetryEntry } from './telemetry-writer.js'`).\n74\t\n75\t### TelemetryEntry Interface\n76\t\n77\t```typescript\n78\texport interface TelemetryEntry {\n79\t  version: 1;\n80\t  timestamp: string;           // ISO 8601\n81\t  storyKey: string;            // e.g., \"16-3-telemetry-writer\"\n82\t  epicId: string;              // e.g., \"16\" (extracted from storyKey)\n83\t  duration_ms: number;         // from ctx.durationMs\n84\t  cost_usd: number | null;     // from ctx.cost (0 if no cost tracked)\n85\t  attempts: number | null;     // not available in TaskContext — set null\n86\t  acResults: ACResult[] | null; // from output contract if available\n87\t  filesChanged: string[];      // from output contract if available, else []\n88\t  testResults: TestResultsSummary | null; // from output contract if available\n89\t  errors: string[];            // empty array if no errors\n90\t}\n91\t```\n92\t\n93\t### Extracting epicId from storyKey\n94\t\n95\tThe `TaskContext.storyKey` follows the pattern `{epicNum}-{storyNum}-{slug}` (e.g., `\"16-3-telemetry-writer\"`). Extract `epicId` by splitting on `-` and taking the first segment. For the sentinel `\"__run__\"` key, set `epicId` to `\"unknown\"`.\n96\t\n97\t### Data Extraction from TaskContext\n98\t\n99\tThe `TaskContext` provides:\n100\t- `storyKey` — directly mapped\n101\t- `durationMs` — mapped to `duration_ms`\n102\t- `cost` — mapped to `cost_usd` (accumulated cost, may be 0)\n103\t- `outputContract` — if non-null, extract `changedFiles`, `testResults`, `acceptanceCriteria`\n104\t- `taskName` — not stored in telemetry entry (always `\"telemetry\"`)\n105\t\n106\tFields NOT available in `TaskContext` (set to `null`):\n107\t- `attempts` — retry count is not tracked in TaskContext; set to null\n108\t- `errors` — no error list in TaskContext; set to empty array `[]`\n109\t\n110\t### File Location\n111\t\n112\tTelemetry file: `{projectDir}/.codeharness/telemetry.jsonl`\n113\t\n114\tUse `ctx.projectDir` from `TaskContext` to resolve the path. The `.codeharness/` directory is already used for workflow state, contracts, and issues — telemetry follows the same pattern.\n115\t\n116\t### Relationship to Story 16-2\n117\t\n118\tStory 16-2 created:\n119\t- `src/lib/null-task-registry.ts` with `TaskContext`, `NullTaskResult`, `NullTaskHandler` types\n120\t- A no-op `telemetry` handler placeholder (line 94-96)\n121\t- `executeNullTask()` in `workflow-engine.ts` that calls handlers from the registry\n122\t\n123\tThis story replaces the no-op with a real implementation. The `TaskContext` interface is already defined and stable. No engine changes needed — only the handler implementation and registry update.\n124\t\n125\t### Performance Requirement (NFR3)\n126\t\n127\t`appendFileSync` for a single NDJSON line (~500 bytes) completes well under 10ms. No buffering or batching needed. The synchronous API is intentional — telemetry writes are infrequent (once per story) and must not be lost on crash.\n128\t\n129\t### Forward Compatibility (version field)\n130\t\n131\tThe `version: 1` field enables future schema changes. If a future version adds fields or changes semantics, readers can branch on `version`. Always serialize `version` first in the JSON object for human readability.\n132\t\n133\t### Project Structure Notes\n134\t\n135\t- Source: `src/lib/telemetry-writer.ts`\n136\t- Tests: `src/lib/__tests__/telemetry-writer.test.ts`\n137\t- Build: TypeScript compiled to `dist/`\n138\t- Test runner: vitest\n139\t- Existing patterns: see `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` for `.codeharness/` directory creation pattern (`mkdirSync` with `{ recursive: true }`)\n140\t\n141\t### References\n142\t\n143\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 16.3]\n144\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 5 — engine-handled null tasks]\n145\t- [Source: src/lib/null-task-registry.ts — TaskContext interface, no-op telemetry placeholder]\n146\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — OutputContract, TestResults, ACStatus interfaces]\n147\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-state.ts — .codeharness directory pattern]\n148\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-2-engine-handled-null-tasks.md — previous story context]\n149\t\n150\t### Previous Story (16-2) Intelligence\n151\t\n152\t- `null-task-registry.ts` created with clean registry pattern. The `telemetry` handler is the first real handler to replace the placeholder.\n153\t- `TaskContext` includes `projectDir` — use this to resolve the telemetry file path (do NOT hardcode or use `process.cwd()`).\n154\t- `NullTaskResult` has `success: boolean` and optional `output: string`. The engine throws `NULL_TASK_FAILED` if `success: false`.\n155\t- `clearNullTaskRegistry()` exists for test isolation — tests should call this, then re-register the telemetry handler.\n156\t- Code review added error handling: handler exceptions are caught and wrapped as `NULL_TASK_HANDLER_ERROR`. The telemetry handler should not need a try/catch — let the engine handle errors.\n157\t- All 4676+ tests pass. Do not break existing tests.\n158\t\n159\t### Git Intelligence\n160\t\n161\tRecent commits:\n162\t- `07e94a2 feat: story 16-2 — engine-handled null tasks` — registry + engine integration\n163\t- `e3c4761 feat: story 16-1 — hierarchical flow schema & parser` — schema + parser\n164\t- Commit pattern: `feat: story {N}-{M} — {title}`\n165\t- Tests always run before commit. Coverage must remain at target.\n166\t\n167\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n168\t## Verification Requirements\n169\t\n170\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/16-3-telemetry-writer-proof.md)\n171\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n172\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n173\t\n174\t## Documentation Requirements\n175\t\n176\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n177\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/16-3-telemetry-writer.md\n178\t\n179\t## Testing Requirements\n180\t\n181\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n182\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n183\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n184\t\n185\t## Dev Agent Record\n186\t\n187\t### Agent Model Used\n188\t\n189\t{{agent_model_name_version}}\n190\t\n191\t### Debug Log References\n192\t\n193\t### Completion Notes List\n194\t\n195\t### File List\n196\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014KEN5emub6zvnw37GStEgR","session_id":"3330d992-072a-4898-af8b-5f3f7e12cbac","uuid":"62636ecc-2e87-40b0-bddf-7191a991db21","timestamp":"2026-04-03T17:41:47.524Z"}
