{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Bzo2w9j81V66WHmrZox7g9","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 3)\n2\t\n3\t### 16-3-telemetry-writer — create-story (2026-04-03T17:39)\n4\t\n5\t- No config.yaml found at `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` — workflow references it but doesn't exist. Not critical.\n6\t- Sprint-status.yaml not updated by subagent per instruction. Still shows backlog.\n7\t- No web research needed — pure node:fs/node:path module.\n8\t- `attempts` field gap — TaskContext doesn't include retry count. Telemetry will have `attempts: null` until future story extends TaskContext.\n9\t\n10\tToken Report: 16 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 8, Glob: 3, Grep: 4, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 10 unique files, 10 total reads. No redundancy.\n11\t\n12\t### 16-3-telemetry-writer — dev-story (2026-04-03T17:44)\n13\t\n14\tNo issues reported. Clean implementation — 18/18 tests pass, 26/26 existing tests pass.\n15\t\n16\tToken Report: 16 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 4, Edit: 8, Write: 2). 5 unique files, 5 total reads. No redundancy.\n17\t\n18\t### 16-3-telemetry-writer — code-review (2026-04-03T17:55)\n19\t\n20\t- HIGH: `clearNullTaskRegistry` JSDoc claims it re-registers built-in handlers but does not. Fixed.\n21\t- MEDIUM: `readTelemetryForEpic` defaulted to `process.cwd()` — made `projectDir` required.\n22\t- MEDIUM: `TestResultsSummary` duplicated `TestResults` type. Fixed with type alias.\n23\t- MEDIUM: Unused imports in test. Fixed.\n24\t- MEDIUM: null-task-registry.test.ts re-registered fake no-op instead of real handler. Fixed.\n25\t- MEDIUM (pre-existing): stats.test.ts assertion mismatch. Fixed.\n26\t- LOW (not fixed): `cost ?? null` is dead code (cost is never undefined).\n27\t- LOW (not fixed): Unnecessary optional chain on `contract?.acceptanceCriteria`.\n28\t- Coverage: 96.58% overall, all files above 80% floor.\n29\t- 4737 tests pass, 0 failures.\n30\t\n31\tToken Report: 35 tool calls (Bash: 20, Read: 8, Edit: 7, Grep: 5, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 11 unique files, 13 reads. Ran coverage 3 times.\n32\t\n33\t### 16-3-telemetry-writer — verify (2026-04-03T18:06)\n34\t\n35\t- ALL_PASS: 10/10 ACs verified with test and code evidence.\n36\t- `codeharness verify` failed on documentation gate: AGENTS.md missing entries for telemetry-writer.ts and null-task-registry.ts. Not an AC issue.\n37\t- Coverage: telemetry-writer.ts 100% Stmts, 93.75% Branch, 100% Funcs, 100% Lines.\n38\t- Branch gap: line 86 catch block empty path in readTelemetryForEpic uncovered (minor).\n39\t- 30 pre-existing tsc errors in unrelated files.\n40\t\n41\tToken Report: 11 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 4, Write: 1). 4 unique files. No redundancy.\n42\t\n43\t### 16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser — create-story (2026-04-03T16:39)\n44\t\n45\t- Config file at `_bmad/config.yaml` not `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` as workflow implied\n46\t- No `project-context.md` exists in repo — skipped\n47\t- Decomposed bundled epic ACs into 11 separate ACs for testability\n48\t- Added ACs #9 (flow/story_flow mutual exclusivity), #10 (agent: null), #11 (scope: per-epic) — implied by architecture but not explicit in epic\n49\t- Risk: `additionalProperties: false` in schema requires careful extension\n50\t- Risk: `oneOf` for flow/story_flow mutual exclusivity may be complex with Ajv — simpler to validate in TypeScript\n51\t- All 11 ACs tagged `test-provable`\n52\t\n53\tToken Report: 23 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 10, Glob: 7, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 12 unique files, 12 total reads. No redundancy.\n54\t\n55\t### 16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser — dev-story (2026-04-03T16:48)\n56\t\n57\t- Pre-existing test failure: `commands/__tests__/stats.test.ts` — unrelated to this story\n58\t- Pre-existing TS errors in `run.test.ts`, `issue.test.ts`, `verdict-parser.test.ts` — unrelated\n59\t- Used Python script for bulk-replace of ~60 inline workflow objects in `workflow-engine.test.ts` with `makeWorkflow()` wrappers\n60\t- Schema vs code enforcement: `flow`/`story_flow` mutual exclusivity enforced in parser code, not JSON Schema `oneOf` (draft-07 creates confusing errors)\n61\t- `execution` object has `additionalProperties: false` — future config additions require schema changes\n62\t- 4676 tests passed, 1 pre-existing failure\n63\t\n64\tToken Report: 33 tool calls (Bash: 10, Read: 11, Edit: 15, Grep: 5, Write: 2, Glob: 2, Skill: 1). 12 unique files, 14 total reads. No redundancy.\n65\t\n66\t### 16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser — code-review (2026-04-03T16:57)\n67\t\n68\t- HIGH: `resolveHierarchicalFlow` accepted arbitrary types without validation — could produce malformed objects. Fixed with `resolveExecutionConfig()` and `normalizeFlowArray()`.\n69\t- MEDIUM: Operator precedence issue in `workflow-parser.ts` with `as` cast + `??`. Fixed.\n70\t- MEDIUM: `run.ts` null guard used `!== null` instead of `!= null`. Fixed.\n71\t- MEDIUM: 4 missing test cases for loop blocks and strategy validation error paths. Added.\n72\t- LOW (not fixed): Duplicate `flow`/`story_flow` coexistence check in two files (defense-in-depth).\n73\t- LOW (not fixed): `resolveHierarchicalFlow` silently returns empty storyFlow when no flow provided.\n74\t- `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` command is broken (pre-existing coverage parser bug).\n75\t- Tests: 28 → 43 (+15 new). 4691 passed, 1 pre-existing failure.\n76\t\n77\tToken Report: 28 tool calls (Bash: 16, Read: 8, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 2, Skill: 1). 10 unique files. ~4 redundant Bash calls trying to parse coverage output.\n78\t\n79\t### 16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser — verify (2026-04-03T17:05)\n80\t\n81\t- ALL_PASS: 11/11 ACs verified with test evidence\n82\t- `codeharness verify` initially failed on preconditions: AGENTS.md missing `hierarchical-flow.ts`, proof format headers wrong (`### AC #N:` vs `## AC N:`)\n83\t- Fixed: AGENTS.md entries for `hierarchical-flow.ts` and `drivers.ts`, proof header format, session state flags\n84\t- Pre-existing: `stats.test.ts` failure, lint 1 error + 52 warnings (all outside story scope)\n85\t- Coverage: `hierarchical-flow.ts` at 100% across all metrics\n86\t- Redundancy: Coverage run executed 3 times with different grep filters before usable output\n87\t\n88\tToken Report (verify subagent): 17 tool calls (Bash: 11, Read: 3, Grep: 3, Write: 1). 4 unique files. Coverage run redundancy.\n89\tToken Report (fix subagent): ~46 tool calls. Fixed AGENTS.md, proof format, state flags.\n90\t\n91\t### 16-2-engine-handled-null-tasks — create-story (2026-04-03T17:10)\n92\t\n93\t- No `project-context.md` file exists in the repo. Not a blocker.\n94\t- `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` path in workflow.yaml is inaccurate — actual is `_bmad/config.yaml`\n95\t- Risk: AC #6 (<10ms performance) may be flaky in CI under load — should use generous threshold\n96\t- `checkDriverHealth()` needs null-agent skip — if missed, engine will try to instantiate driver for null tasks\n97\t- run.ts fix for null agents already done in story 16-1 (line 141). Task 3 is verification-only.\n98\t- All 8 ACs tagged test-provable\n99\t\n100\tToken Report: 20 tool calls (Read: 11, Grep: 2, Glob: 4, Bash: 3, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 13 unique files, 13 total reads. No redundancy.\n101\t\n102\t### 16-2-engine-handled-null-tasks — dev-story (2026-04-03T17:17)\n103\t\n104\t- Workaround: `executeNullTask` throws plain `EngineError` object (not Error subclass) for NULL_TASK_NOT_FOUND. Added `isEngineError()` type guard. Inconsistent with `DispatchError` which extends Error. Future cleanup should make EngineError a proper Error subclass.\n105\t- Code quality: Null task branches in `executeWorkflow()` and `executeLoopBlock()` duplicate scope-handling logic. Could be refactored to generic \"execute task for scope\" function.\n106\t- Edge case: `cost` field in `TaskContext` only carries forward previous task's `cost_usd`, not accumulated total. Story spec says \"total cost so far\" but engine doesn't track cumulative cost.\n107\t- run.ts line 141 already has